

=Definition=

"A form of online journalism which utilizes version control systems (VCS)
for the purposes of contemporaneous time-stamping and tracking changes
to a story. Ideally, this model would be implemented using open-source
intelligence (OSINT), open-source software (OSS), and “copyleft” or
Creative Commons (CC) licensing within an open participatory network."
(https://einzelgaengerinmotte.files.wordpress.com/2018/02/revision-controlled_journalism_v2.pdf)


